<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>URL Shortener</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      margin: 0;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      animation: fadeDown 0.8s ease;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      color: #333;
      animation: fadeUp 0.8s ease;
    }

    a.cta {
      display: inline-block;
      background-color: #000;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 15px 35px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      box-shadow: 4px 4px 0px #000;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
      animation: fadeUp 1s ease;
    }

    a.cta:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px #000;
    }

    footer {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 20px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #777;
      animation: fadeUp 1.2s ease;
    }

    @keyframes fadeDown {
      0% {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(-20px);
      }
      100% {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }
    }

    @keyframes fadeUp {
      0% {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(20px);
      }
      100% {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to Trimly</h1>
  <p>
    The simple, fast and privacy-friendly way to shorten your long URLs.
    Create a short link in seconds and track its clicks with ease.
  </p>
  <a href="/url" class="cta">Trim Your URL Now</a>

  <footer>© <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Trimly – All rights reserved.</footer>
</body>
</html>
